author: Katrina Tulloch | ktulloch@syracuse.com
title: Enchanted Beaver Lake sold out for 2015 season
text:
Comments 
BALDWINSVILLE, N.Y. -- The wildly popular Enchanted Beaver Lake celebration for Halloween has sold out in advance ticket sales for this weekend. 
From Thursday to Sunday, Beaver Lake Nature Center features two trails lit by over 500 jack-o-lanterns and 500 luminaria. Volunteers (aged 14 or older) have been carving the pumpkins since last Saturday. The nature center provides all the pumpkins, tools and stencils. 
Visitors with advance tickets will also enjoy face-painting, fortune telling, autumn treats and family-friendly ghost stories. 
Robin O'Gallo of Onondaga County Parks said people cannot pay more at the door to get in to Enchanted Beaver Lake. If people show up without their advance tickets, they will be turned away. 
For more information, call the Nature Center at 638-2519 or visit OnondagaCountyParks.com . 
For those with advance tickets: Where: Beaver Lake Nature Center at 8477 East Mud Lake Rd. When: Thursday, Oct. 22 through Sunday, Oct. 25 from 6 to 8:30 p.m. on all four nights. Drop offs are not allowed, nor is parking along East Mud Lake Road.
